BFN [Text] The budget session of the National Assembly began at the Parliament House in Islamabad today.
 The speaker, Syed Yusuf Raza Gilani, is chairing the session.
 The opposition, ending their boycott of the National Assembly, participated in the proceedings of the house today.
 Speaking during question hour, the prime minister, Ms. Benazir Bhutto, said strict action will be taken against those responsible for the fire incident in the parliament building.
 She said her government believes in the rule of law and nobody is above the law.
 Committees and commissions were formed in the past, but no action was taken.
 The prime minister said the present government has launched a moral crusade and nobody will be spared.
 The prime minister, Ms. Benazir Bhutto, has welcomed the opposition's decision to end the boycott of the National Assembly and described it as a positive step.
 Talking to newsmen at the Parliament House in Islamabad this afternoon, Ms. Benazir Bhutto said she had advised the opposition two days earlier to end their boycott and fulfill their constitutional responsibilities as elected representatives.
 She said she would also respond positively and invite the opposition leader and leaders of other political parties for discussions on economic issues over a cup of tea.
 